"""rAIdio.bot fairseq replacement — minimal package surface.

ComfyUI-RVC imports fairseq for HuBERT feature extraction during voice
training. The real fairseq cannot be built on this Windows embedded
Python (no Python.h). This package replaces the previous always-raise
stub with a working implementation:

  - fairseq.checkpoint_utils.load_model_ensemble_and_task(paths) loads
    a fairseq HuBERT-base checkpoint, remaps state_dict keys to the
    HuggingFace transformers HubertModel format, and returns an
    object exposing the fairseq-style extract_features() API.

  - The other submodules (data, dataclass, modules, tasks, models) are
    minimal stubs that exist only so torch.load can find class names
    referenced inside the fairseq checkpoint pickle. None of those
    classes are actually instantiated for inference; their only purpose
    is to satisfy the unpickler.

Surface area is intentionally narrow — only what ComfyUI-RVC's
extract_feature_print.py exercises (load_model_ensemble_and_task +
model.extract_features + saved_cfg.task.normalize). Everything else
returns None or a no-op.

License: GPL-3.0 — matches fairseq upstream and the GPL-3.0 PyTorch
ecosystem this patches into.
Source: https://github.com/rAIdio-bot/rAIdio-nodes
"""

# Eagerly expose checkpoint_utils so `from fairseq import checkpoint_utils`
# AND `import fairseq; fairseq.checkpoint_utils.load_...` both work.
from . import checkpoint_utils  # noqa: F401
